xample, a substantial interpretation of Locke and discussions of Kant, Adam Smith, Edmund Burke, Jeremy Bentham, and J.S. Mill. Introduced by Shirley Robin Letwin, who attended the lectures, the book provides a compact introduction to ideas that Oakeshott developed more elaborately in other writings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCollectivism. 0aIndividualism. 0aPolitical ethics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aMinogue, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300237740?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300237740423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300237740/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles